# LoadZone Admin Shell

- The authenticated admin shell must be centered on a single `activeTeam`.
- Resolve `activeTeam` from one central server helper and validate it against accessible teams.
- Do not introduce new daily operational views that mix multiple teams in the same screen.
- Desktop sidebar and mobile bottom navigation must share the same primary navigation config.
- Keep `Dashboard`, `Wellness`, `Sesiones`, and `ConfiguraciĂ³n` as the only primary destinations.
- Treat `Players`, `Seasons`, `Injuries`, and `Analysis` as secondary surfaces reachable from menus or contextual links.
- Prefer club/team branding in the shell with `Team.logoUrl` first and `Club.logoUrl` as fallback.
- Keep shell-specific mobile navigation in `apps/app`; shared primitives in `packages/design-system` must remain app-agnostic.
